🖼️ Screenshot Summary

## GUI Mode — sfs_gui.py

Shows the Secure File Storage (SFS) graphical interface.
Users can easily choose files, load or generate keyfiles, and perform encryption or decryption through simple buttons.

Example Command:

python sfs_gui.py

Features:

Choose multiple files for encryption/decryption

Load or generate a secure keyfile

Create a vault from multiple files

Simple and user-friendly interface



---

## CLI Mode — Encryption & Decryption

Demonstrates how to encrypt and decrypt files via terminal using the command-line version of the tool.

Example Commands:

# Encrypt file and store output in a custom directory
python sfs_cli.py encrypt --in-file myfile.txt --password MyStrongPass --out-dir encrypted_files/

# Decrypt the encrypted file
python sfs_cli.py decrypt --in-file encrypted_files/myfile.txt.enc --password MyStrongPass --out-dir decrypted_files/

Result:

> File successfully encrypted and decrypted — integrity check: ✅ True




---

## CLI Mode — Quick Encryption Example

Shows a simple one-line encryption using password authentication.

Example Command:

python sfs_cli.py encrypt --in-file myfile.txt --password MyStrongPass --out myfile.txt.enc

Result:

> Encrypted: myfile.txt.enc
Fast and secure — perfect for single-file protection.




